@page "/privacy"
@layout MainLayout

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy - Play2Day</PageTitle>

<section class="legal-page">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 40px 20px;">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p><em>Last updated: @DateTime.UtcNow.ToString("d MMMM yyyy")</em></p>

        <p>
            This notice explains how Play2Day handles your personal data when you use our website
            and services. The data controller is Play2Day. For any privacy questions or to
            exercise your rights, contact us at
            <a href="mailto:privacy@play2day.com">privacy@play2day.com</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>What we collect</h2>
        <p>
            When you make a booking or contact us, we may collect your name, contact details, and
            booking information. When you use our staff systems, we process your account and
            attendance information. Our servers also record technical data such as IP addresses for
            security purposes.
        </p>

        <h2>Why we use it</h2>
        <p>
            We use your data to provide and manage our services (bookings, accounts), to meet our
            legal obligations, and to keep our systems secure. These rely on the legal bases of
            contract, legal obligation, and our legitimate interests.
        </p>

        <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
        <p>
            We keep personal data only for as long as necessary for the purposes above and to meet
            our legal obligations, after which it is deleted or anonymised.
        </p>

        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>
            You have the right to access, correct, delete, or restrict the use of your personal
            data, and to object to processing. To exercise any of these, email
            <a href="mailto:privacy@play2day.com">privacy@play2day.com</a>. You may also complain
            to the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO).
        </p>

        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>
            We use only strictly-necessary cookies. See our <a href="/cookies">Cookie Policy</a>
            for details.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>
